--- /cleanup_gitlab_branches.py
+++ /cleanup_gitlab_branches.py
@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@
+#!/usr/bin/env python3
+import requests
+import urllib.parse
@@ -1,0 +5,68 @@
+GITLAB_URL = "http://the-agent-company.com:8929"
+API_URL = f"{GITLAB_URL}/api/v4"
+USERNAME = "root"
+PASSWORD = "theagentcompany"
+auth = (USERNAME, PASSWORD)
+
+
+def get_projects(page=1):
+    params = {"per_page": 100, "page": page, "archived": "false"}
+    response = requests.get(f"{API_URL}/projects", auth=auth, params=params)
+    if response.status_code == 200:
+        return response.json()
+    else:
+        print(f"Error getting projects: {response.text}")
+        return []
+
+
+def get_branches(project_id, page=1):
+    params = {"per_page": 100, "page": page}
+    response = requests.get(f"{API_URL}/projects/{project_id}/repository/branches", auth=auth, params=params)
+    if response.status_code == 200:
+        return response.json()
+    else:
+        print(f"Error getting branches for project {project_id}: {response.text}")
+        return []
+
+
+def delete_branch(project_id, branch_name):
+    branch_encoded = urllib.parse.quote(branch_name, safe='')
+    response = requests.delete(f"{API_URL}/projects/{project_id}/repository/branches/{branch_encoded}", auth=auth)
+    if response.status_code == 204:
+        print(f"Deleted branch '{branch_name}' in project {project_id}")
+    else:
+        print(f"Failed to delete branch '{branch_name}' in project {project_id}: {response.status_code} {response.text}")
+
+
+def main():
+    page = 1
+    while True:
+        projects = get_projects(page)
+        if not projects:
+            break
+        for project in projects:
+            project_id = project["id"]
+            if project.get("archived", False):
+                print(f"Skipping archived project {project_id}")
+                continue
+            default_branch = project.get("default_branch")
+            if not default_branch:
+                print(f"No default branch for project {project_id}, skipping.")
+                continue
+            bpage = 1
+            while True:
+                branches = get_branches(project_id, bpage)
+                if not branches:
+                    break
+                for branch in branches:
+                    branch_name = branch["name"]
+                    if branch_name != default_branch:
+                        print(f"Deleting branch '{branch_name}' from project {project_id} (default branch is '{default_branch}')")
+                        delete_branch(project_id, branch_name)
+                bpage += 1
+        page += 1
+
+
+if __name__ == "__main__":
+    main()
+
